  "prompt": "How long does it take an iStockphoto photography contributor application to be processed?",
  "response": "The processing time for an iStockphoto (now part of Getty Images) contributor application can vary, but it typically takes **2-4 weeks** for your application to be reviewed and approved or rejected. However, this timeline can be longer during peak periods or if there are issues with your submission that require additional review.\n\n### Factors that may affect processing time:\n1. **Volume of Applications**: High volumes of submissions can slow down the review process.\n2. **Quality and Completeness of Submission**: If your application is incomplete or your samples don't meet their standards, it may take longer to process.\n3. **Review Process**: Getty Images has strict quality and technical standards, so they carefully assess each application.\n\nTo increase your chances of a smooth and timely approval:\n- Ensure your portfolio meets their technical and creative standards.\n- Submit high-quality, commercially viable images.\n- Follow all guidelines and requirements provided in the application process.\n\nIf your application is taking longer than expected, you can reach out to Getty Images' contributor support for an update. Keep in mind that patience is key, as the review process is thorough to maintain their high standards.",
